<subSubSection id="11C46515FFFBFFEEFF523507347B97AB" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5961369EFFFBFFEEFF523507347B97AB" blockId="0.[151,1436,1561,1723]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis id="6BAAEA8CFFFBFFEEFF523507365C9721" bold="true" box="[151,268,1561,1585]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This genus can be distinguished from other araneids by the long and granulated carapace in males and females (
<figureCitation id="C1E52A1BFFFBFFEEFF3C352236339743" box="[249,355,1596,1619]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1242,1265]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,187,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,181,1230]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 1, Male habitus, dorsal view; 2, female habitus, dorsal view; 3, male pedipalp, prolateral view; 4, ditto, retrolateral view; 5, female abdomen, ventral view; 7, ditto, antero-ventral view (arrow points to anterior tubercles). Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277031/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Figs. 1, 2</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="3D4F4B6FFFFBFFEEFEB5352235669743" author="Santos" box="[368,566,1596,1619]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" refString="Santos, A. J., Brescovit, A. D. &amp; Levi, H. W. (2005) Melychiopharis: an atypical orb-weaving spider from South America (Araneae: Araneidae). Zootaxa, 1016, 57 - 64." type="journal article" year="2005">
Santos 
<emphasis id="6BAAEA8CFFFBFFEEFE7B352236A69743" box="[446,502,1596,1619]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">et al.</emphasis>
<number id="EF1624B9FFFBFFEEFE38352235669743" box="[509,566,1596,1619]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: figs. 
<number id="EF1624B9FFFBFFEEFDBD352235F29743" box="[632,674,1596,1619]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
). The male pedipalp is distinctive in the embolus arising from a large, rounded base and in the filiform, long and proximally directed median apophysis (
<figureCitation id="C1E52A1BFFFBFFEEFC3B354133339766" box="[1022,1123,1631,1654]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1242,1265]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,187,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,181,1230]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 1, Male habitus, dorsal view; 2, female habitus, dorsal view; 3, male pedipalp, prolateral view; 4, ditto, retrolateral view; 5, female abdomen, ventral view; 7, ditto, antero-ventral view (arrow points to anterior tubercles). Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277031/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Figs. 3, 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C1E52A1BFFFBFFEEFBA8354133C79766" box="[1133,1175,1631,1654]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1311,1334]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,592,1279]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,583,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 10. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 7, Male pedipalp, prolateral view; 8, ditto, retrolateral view; 9, female epigynum, ventral view; 10, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; M, median plate of epigynum; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium; SP, spermathecae. Scale bars: 4.7 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277032/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">7, 8</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="3D4F4B6FFFFBFFEEFB66354132339766" author="Santos" box="[1187,1379,1631,1654]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" refString="Santos, A. J., Brescovit, A. D. &amp; Levi, H. W. (2005) Melychiopharis: an atypical orb-weaving spider from South America (Araneae: Araneidae). Zootaxa, 1016, 57 - 64." type="journal article" year="2005">
Santos 
<emphasis id="6BAAEA8CFFFBFFEEFB35354132759766" box="[1264,1317,1631,1654]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">et al.</emphasis>
<number id="EF1624B9FFFBFFEEFAEF354132339766" box="[1322,1379,1631,1654]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: figs. 
<number id="EF1624B9FFFBFFEEFF52359C37929789" box="[151,194,1666,1689]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" value="7.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="6.0">6–8</number>
). Epigynum is relatively simple, with a rounded median plate and copulatory ducts laterally visible by transparency through the tegument (
<figureCitation id="C1E52A1BFFFBFFEEFE4C35BA36BF97AB" box="[393,495,1700,1723]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1242,1265]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,187,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,181,1230]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 1, Male habitus, dorsal view; 2, female habitus, dorsal view; 3, male pedipalp, prolateral view; 4, ditto, retrolateral view; 5, female abdomen, ventral view; 7, ditto, antero-ventral view (arrow points to anterior tubercles). Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277031/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Figs. 5, 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C1E52A1BFFFBFFEEFE3E35BA355B97AB" box="[507,523,1700,1723]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1311,1334]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,592,1279]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,583,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 10. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 7, Male pedipalp, prolateral view; 8, ditto, retrolateral view; 9, female epigynum, ventral view; 10, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; M, median plate of epigynum; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium; SP, spermathecae. Scale bars: 4.7 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277032/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
<number id="EF1624B9FFFBFFEEFE3E35BA355B97AB" box="[507,523,1700,1723]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="3D4F4B6FFFFBFFEEFDD335BA358997AB" author="Santos" box="[534,729,1700,1723]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" refString="Santos, A. J., Brescovit, A. D. &amp; Levi, H. W. (2005) Melychiopharis: an atypical orb-weaving spider from South America (Araneae: Araneidae). Zootaxa, 1016, 57 - 64." type="journal article" year="2005">
